[RotationNote "Board 1, chOption: N, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:0, nBasis: 0, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "da29f677d285036671e70d96696f4387d39973bdd7bb8b4117c80bcdadb829e8"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/fourth_suit_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{With 14 points you will insist on game, but you aren't strong enough to jump shift. So you bid 1\H. Partner rebids 1\S.  

Partner shows nothing extra. All you know now is that he doesn't have 4 \Hs. You know you want to be in game, but you aren't sure which game. If partner has 3 \Hs then 4\H would be good. If not though, 3NT would be good if he has a \D stopper. The way to find out what he has is with Fourth Suit Forcing. So you bid 2\D. Partner answers with 2NT.  

Partner does not have 3 \Hs, but he does have \Ds stopped. So you bid 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:6.AJT.QT954.AQ73 J93.KQ75.87.T652 AK752.863.AK.984 QT84.942.J632.KJ"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1D pass 1S pass 2C pass 2H pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "c1b7640fba17416089f8d971b6c0cdc721a66b37db288977fa3e99d7c866af3d"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/fourth_suit_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{You open your 5-card suit, 1\D. Partner responds 1\S.  

You might bid 1NT, but since you have a singleton you prefer to say 2\C.

Partner bids 2\H.  

This is Fourth Suit Forcing and partner is fishing for more information. You certainly don't have 3 of his \Ss so that is out. On the other hand, you have a double stopper in \Hs, so with 14 points you go right to 3NT.}

